Why GPL-3.0 here:

* Blender is licensed under GPL-2+. Any Python script that ``import bpy``
  becomes a derivative work of Blender and must be distributed under a
  compatible GPL license. GPL-3.0-or-later is the most current compatible
  choice.
* The ``erre-sandbox`` Python library at ../src/erre_sandbox/ is
  Apache-2.0 OR MIT. It does NOT ``import bpy`` and does NOT depend on
  anything in this directory at runtime — it only consumes the exported
  ``.glb`` artefacts, which are data files covered by CC-BY or CC0
  depending on the authoring source.
* Keeping this package physically separate is how the project preserves
  its dual license. See ``README.md`` §"Why a separate package?".

